Description:
The Zeiss Victory RF Rangefinder Binoculars is the most advanced laser rangefinding binocular on the market. The 10x54 gives the user enhanced optical performance via the unique 54mm objective lens, a wide field of view and comfortable viewing experience. New SMART technology provides Bluetooth connectivity allowing the user to send their ballistic data from the Zeiss Hunting App to the Victory RF, which then displays the user's ballistic data in one of (7) different options: straight-line distance to target, actual horizontal distance to target if shooting at an incline/decline, range + angle, MOA adjustment, MIL adjustment, or Click adjustments. The new RF includes temperature, air pressure, and angle sensors to give the shooter the most data possible. The bright red LED display can be adjusted on the Zeiss Hunting App and sent to the RF, or can be manually adjusted with (5) different brightness settings, assuring the user of an easily legible display at all times of day. The highly-precise and accurate rangefinder easily ranges targets past 2,000 yards and up to 2,500 yards in some settings. Ergonomics - the new Victory RF is by far the most ergonomic and easy-to-use rangefinding binocular, built on our Victory HT frame and containing no bumps, humps, or awkward design features. The ranging and feature buttons lie on the inside of each binocular barrel, making it extremely easy and intuitive to range targets and adjust settings while in the field. Additionally, for right or left handers, the function for each button can be switched so that the ranging/settings button are on either the left or the right side. One-Touch-Principle means with one simple touch of the ranging button the user gets a lightning-quick, accurate range. No longer is it necessary to hit the ranging button multiple times, wasting time and creating more shake of the binocular. Optics - the inclusion of Schott HT (High-Transmission) glass and specialized T lens coatings customized for each lens surface creates leading brightness and sharpness of image. This is simply a lightweight, compact, easy to use high-performance binocular with an unbelievable rangefinder inside. Made In Germany.
